.c-content

    h1 Cards

    p A card is a common UI pattern. A card can hold information. Cards are used to separate page content into logical sections. A card can consist of a card header, a card body, and a card footer.

    p This is the simplest card possible:

.br-sample
    .br-sample-content
        .c-card
            .c-card__body
                p Card content

.c-content
    p A card usually has a header:

.br-sample
    .br-sample-content
        .c-card
            .c-card__header
                h3.c-card__title Title of the card
            .c-card__body
                p Card content

.c-content
    p Multiple card bodies are also possible.

.br-sample
    .br-sample-content
        .c-card
            .c-card__header
                h3.c-card__title Title of the card
            .c-card__body
                p Card body 1
            .c-card__body
                p Card body 2

.c-content
    p You can swap out a card body with a table (without its table heading section), but only if the table data is clear enough on its own.

.br-sample
    .br-sample-content
        .c-card
            .c-card__header
                h3.c-card__title Title of the card
            table.c-table.c-table--styled.c-table--bordered
                tbody
                    tr
                        td Data
                        td Data
                        td Data
                    tr
                        td Data
                        td Data
                        td Data
                    tr
                        td Data
                        td Data
                        td Data

